<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>{{ service_name }} MCP</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Connect {{ service_name }} to Claude, Cursor, or any MCP-compatible AI tool and access your data directly from your AI workflow.">
    <style>
        @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap');

        :root {
            --primary:      #1a56db;
            --primary-hover:#1648c2;
            --charcoal:     #212529;
            --grey:         #6c757d;
            --border:       #dee2e6;
            --white:        #ffffff;
            --light-bg:     #f0f4ff;
            --hero-grad:    linear-gradient(170deg, #ffffff 0%, #e8eeff 60%, #d8e4ff 100%);
        }

        *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
            font-size: 16px;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: var(--charcoal);
            background: var(--white);
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 1140px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 0 2.7rem;
        }

        /* ── Sticky Header ── */
        header {
            position: sticky;
            top: 0;
            z-index: 100;
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
            backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
            -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        }

        .header-inner {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: space-between;
            padding: 0.9rem 0;
        }

        .logo-link {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            text-decoration: none;
            gap: 0.5rem;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: var(--charcoal);
        }

        .nav-right {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 1.5rem;
        }

        .nav-right a {
            font-size: 0.95rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            color: var(--charcoal);
            text-decoration: none;
            transition: color 0.2s;
        }

        .nav-right a:hover { color: var(--primary); }

        /* ── Buttons ── */
        .btn-primary {
            display: inline-block;
            background: var(--primary);
            color: #fff;
            font-weight: 600;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
            padding: 0.65rem 1.75rem;
            border-radius: 720px;
            text-decoration: none;
            transition: background 0.2s, transform 0.1s;
            white-space: nowrap;
        }

        .btn-primary:hover {
            background: var(--primary-hover);
            transform: translateY(-1px);
        }

        /* ── Hero ── */
        .hero {
            background: var(--hero-grad);
            padding: 5.5rem 0 4.5rem;
        }

        .hero h1 {
            font-size: 2.75rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            line-height: 1.2;
            color: var(--charcoal);
            margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
            max-width: 680px;
        }

        .hero p {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            color: var(--grey);
            max-width: 600px;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
        }

        /* ── Main content area ── */
        main {
            background: var(--light-bg);
        }

        .content-area {
            padding: 3rem 0 5rem;
        }

        /* ── Cards ── */
        .card {
            background: var(--white);
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 6px;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
            padding: 2.5rem 2.75rem;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        }

        .card h2 {
            font-size: 1.35rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: var(--charcoal);
            margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
        }

        .card h3 {
            font-size: 1.05rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            color: var(--charcoal);
            margin-top: 2rem;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 0.5rem;
        }

        .card h3::before {
            content: '';
            display: inline-block;
            width: 10px;
            height: 10px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            background: var(--primary);
            flex-shrink: 0;
        }

        .card p {
            color: var(--grey);
            font-size: 0.97rem;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

        .card ol, .card ul {
            color: var(--grey);
            font-size: 0.97rem;
            padding-left: 1.4rem;
            margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
        }

        .card li { margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }

        .card strong { color: var(--charcoal); }

        code {
            font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
            font-size: 0.88em;
            background: #f1f3f5;
            color: #c2185b;
            padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem;
            border-radius: 4px;
        }

        .code-block {
            background: #212529;
            color: #f8f9fa;
            border-radius: 6px;
            padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
            overflow-x: auto;
            margin: 0.75rem 0 1.25rem;
        }

        .code-block pre {
            margin: 0;
            white-space: pre-wrap;
            font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
            font-size: 0.88rem;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .section-label {
            display: inline-block;
            font-size: 0.78rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            letter-spacing: 0.05em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--primary);
            background: rgba(26, 86, 219, 0.08);
            border: 1px solid rgba(26, 86, 219, 0.25);
            border-radius: 720px;
            padding: 0.2rem 0.75rem;
            margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
        }

        /* ── Footer ── */
        footer {
            background: var(--white);
            border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
            padding: 2.5rem 0;
        }

        .footer-inner {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: space-between;
            font-size: 0.88rem;
            color: var(--grey);
        }

        .footer-inner a {
            color: var(--grey);
            text-decoration: none;
            transition: color 0.2s;
        }

        .footer-inner a:hover { color: var(--primary); }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- ── Header ── -->
    <header>
        <div class="container header-inner">
            <a href="#" class="logo-link">
                {{ service_name }}
            </a>
            <nav class="nav-right">
                {% raw %}{% if support_email %}<a href="mailto:{{ support_email }}">Get Help</a>{% endif %}{% endraw %}
                <a href="#connect" class="btn-primary">Connect Now</a>
            </nav>
        </div>
    </header>

    <!-- ── Hero ── -->
    <section class="hero">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-label">Model Context Protocol</div>
            <h1>{{ service_name }}, direct to your AI.</h1>
            <p>Connect {{ service_name }} to Claude, Cursor, or any MCP-compatible tool and access your data directly in your AI workflow — no tab switching, no exports.</p>
            <a href="#connect" class="btn-primary">Get Connected →</a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── Main Content ── -->
    <main>
        <div class="container content-area">

            <!-- What is MCP -->
            <div class="card">
                <h2>What is MCP?</h2>
                <p>Model Context Protocol (MCP) is an open standard that lets AI tools connect to external data sources. Think of it as a universal plug — once an AI tool supports MCP it can connect to any MCP server with just a URL, and your AI can access {{ service_name }} data natively without switching tabs.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Before you start -->
            <div class="card">
                <h2>Before you start</h2>
                <p>You'll need a {{ service_name }} account. You will authenticate your AI tool using your existing {{ service_name }} credentials via a secure <strong>OAuth2</strong> flow.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- How to Connect -->
            <div id="connect" class="card">
                <h2>How to Connect</h2>

                <!-- 1. Claude.ai web -->
                <h3>1. Connect via Claude.ai (Web)</h3>
                <p>The simplest setup for teams and individual users.</p>

                <p><strong>For Individual Users:</strong></p>
                <ol>
                    <li>In Claude, go to <strong>Settings → Connectors</strong>.</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>Add → Custom → Web</strong>.</li>
                    <li>Name: <code>{{ service_name }}</code></li>
                    <li>Remote MCP Server URL: <code>{% raw %}{{ mcp_public_url }}{% endraw %}/mcp</code></li>
                    <li>Click <strong>Connect</strong> and follow the OAuth flow.</li>
                </ol>

                <!-- 2. Claude Desktop -->
                <h3>2. Connect via Claude Desktop</h3>
                <p>Add the following to your <code>claude_desktop_config.json</code>:</p>
                <div class="code-block"><pre>{
  "mcpServers": {
    "{{ project_name }}": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": [
        "-y",
        "mcp-remote@latest",
        "{% raw %}{{ mcp_public_url }}{% endraw %}/mcp"
      ]
    }
  }
}</pre></div>
                <p style="font-size:0.88rem; color:var(--grey);">Config file location (macOS): <code>~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json</code></p>

                <!-- 3. Claude Code CLI -->
                <h3>3. Connect via Claude Code (CLI)</h3>
                <p>Add {{ service_name }} to your current project:</p>
                <div class="code-block"><pre>claude mcp add {{ project_name }} --transport http {% raw %}{{ mcp_public_url }}{% endraw %}/mcp</pre></div>

                <!-- 4. Other clients -->
                <h3>4. Other MCP Clients (Cursor, Windsurf, etc.)</h3>
                <p>Point any MCP-compatible tool to:</p>
                <div class="code-block"><pre>{% raw %}{{ mcp_public_url }}{% endraw %}/mcp</pre></div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </main>

    <!-- ── Footer ── -->
    <footer>
        <div class="container footer-inner">
            <span>&copy; {% raw %}{{ year }}{% endraw %} {{ service_name }}. All rights reserved.</span>
            <div>
                <a href="#">{{ service_name }}</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </footer>

</body>
</html>
